---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Disclaimer"
  description="Disclaimer for Betting Maths, explaining that the site provides educational betting calculators and guides only and does not provide betting tips, predictions or financial advice."
>
  <section class="content-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">Disclaimer</p>
    <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Betting Maths provides educational calculators and plain-English explanations. It does not provide betting tips, predictions, financial advice or guaranteed profit strategies.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Important:</strong> Betting always involves risk. Calculations can help explain possible outcomes, but they cannot guarantee results.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Educational information only</h2>
    <p>
      The information on Betting Maths is provided for general educational and informational purposes. It is designed to help users understand betting maths concepts such as odds, implied probability, overround, bookmaker margin, dutching, hedging, lay liability, free bets, matched betting, each-way betting and Rule 4 deductions.
    </p>
    <p>
      The site should not be treated as professional advice, financial advice, legal advice, tax advice or gambling advice.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>No betting tips or predictions</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths does not recommend specific bets, selections, bookmakers, exchanges, odds or strategies.
    </p>
    <p>
      Any examples used on the site are for illustration only. They are not predictions and should not be treated as recommendations to place a bet.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>No guarantee of profit</h2>
    <p>
      Some betting calculations may show possible profits, reduced-risk outcomes, theoretical arbitrage opportunities or positive estimated values under certain inputs.
    </p>
    <p>
      These are mathematical examples only. Real-world betting outcomes can be affected by many factors, including:
    </p>

    <ul class="standard-list">
      <li>Odds movement</li>
      <li>Market suspension</li>
      <li>Exchange liquidity</li>
      <li>Commission</li>
      <li>Bookmaker rules</li>
      <li>Offer terms and restrictions</li>
      <li>Void bets and settlement differences</li>
      <li>Rule 4 deductions and non-runners</li>
      <li>Dead heat rules</li>
      <li>Human error</li>
      <li>Account restrictions</li>
      <li>Technical issues</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      No calculator or guide on Betting Maths can guarantee profit.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Calculator accuracy</h2>
    <p>
      The calculators on Betting Maths are intended to provide helpful estimates based on the information entered by the user.
    </p>
    <p>
      While the aim is to make the calculations clear and useful, users should always check important figures independently before relying on them. Small differences in rounding, commission, odds format, offer type or settlement rules can change the final result.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Bookmaker and exchange terms</h2>
    <p>
      Betting terms can vary between bookmakers, betting exchanges, markets and promotions.
    </p>
    <p>
      Users should always read the relevant bookmaker or exchange terms before placing a bet. This is especially important for free bets, matched betting offers, each-way terms, extra places, Rule 4 deductions, dead heat rules, cash out offers and promotional restrictions.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Responsible gambling</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths does not encourage users to gamble beyond their means or treat betting as income.
    </p>
    <p>
      If betting stops feeling controlled, affordable or enjoyable, it may be time to stop and seek support.
    </p>

    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button primary" href="/responsible-gambling/">Responsible Gambling</a>
      <a class="button secondary" href="/about/">About Betting Maths</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths may link to third-party websites for further information, support resources or related tools. External websites are controlled by their own owners and may change without notice.
    </p>
    <p>
      A link to an external website does not mean Betting Maths controls or endorses everything on that website.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Advertising and affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      Betting Maths may include advertising, affiliate links or sponsored placements in the future.
    </p>
    <p>
      If affiliate links are added, the site should make this clear where relevant. Affiliate or advertising arrangements should not change the educational nature of the calculators and guides.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-card article-section">
    <h2>Changes to this disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      This disclaimer may be updated as the site develops, especially if new features, advertising, affiliate links, tools or content sections are added.
    </p>
    <p>
      Last updated: 3 May 2026.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style>
    .article-section {
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }

    .standard-list {
      padding-left: 1.3rem;
    }

    .standard-list li {
      margin: 0.45rem 0;
    }

    .article-section a {
      color: var(--color-green-dark);
      font-weight: 800;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
